    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Operating System Design Overview</title>
        <para>The AQUA-OS operating system implements a microkernel architecture with 
        separation kernel capabilities. This design ensures that failures in one partition 
        cannot affect other partitions, meeting the safety requirements for DAL-A systems.</para>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Architectural Components</title>
          <para>The OS consists of the following major components:</para>
          <para>- Separation Kernel: Enforces time and space partitioning</para>
          <para>- Partition Manager: Manages partition lifecycle and scheduling</para>
          <para>- Communication Manager: Inter-partition communication services</para>
          <para>- I/O Manager: Device drivers and I/O services</para>
          <para>- Health Monitor: Fault detection and system health management</para>
        </levelledPara>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Design Principles</title>
          <para>The design follows these key principles:</para>
          <para>- Minimal trusted computing base</para>
          <para>- Separation of concerns between kernel and partitions</para>
          <para>- Deterministic behavior for real-time operations</para>
          <para>- Formal verification of critical properties</para>
        </levelledPara>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
